-- Brazil to Delay Planned Budget Cuts Until After July, Folha Says
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2012-01-21T14:52:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-21/brazil-to-delay-planned-budget-cuts-until-after-july-folha-says.html
Brazilian President  Dilma Rousseff 
may postpone about 60 billion reais ($34.2 billion) of planned
budget cuts until after July because of municipal elections,
Folha de S.Paulo reported, without saying where it obtained the
information.  The government will seek to increase public and private
spending in the first half of the year to revive the economy,
according to the Sao Paulo-based newspaper.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  